US authorities have been on alert for mail with white powder in it since 2001, when envelopes laced with anthrax were sent to media outlets and US lawmakers. NEW YORK - Vanessa Trump, the wife of Donald Trump Jr, was taken to a hospital on Monday after complaining of nausea when she was exposed to an unidentified white powder that came in the mail, a police spokesman said. US authorities have been on alert for mail with white powder in it since 2001, when envelopes laced with anthrax were sent to media outlets and US lawmakers, killing five people.